Class ImagingStudy

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.fhir.model.api.BaseElement
      • ca.uhn.fhir.model.dstu.resource.BaseResource
        • ca.uhn.fhir.model.dstu.resource.ImagingStudy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICompositeElement, IElement, IResource, ISupportsUndeclaredExtensions, IBase, IBaseResource

    public class ImagingStudy
extends BaseResource
implements IResource
    HAPI/FHIR ImagingStudy Resource (A set of images produced in single study (one or more series of references images))

    Definition: Manifest of a set of images produced in study. The set of images may include every image in the study, or it may be an incomplete sample, such as a list of key images

    Requirements:

    Profile Definition: http://hl7.org/fhir/profiles/ImagingStudy

      • addModality

        public BoundCodeDt<ImagingModalityEnum> addModality(ImagingModalityEnum theValue)
        Add a value for modality (All series.modality if actual acquisition modalities) using an enumerated type. This is intended as a convenience method for situations where the FHIR defined ValueSets are mandatory or contain the desirable codes. If you wish to use codes other than those which are built-in, you may also use the addModality() method.

        Definition: A list of all the Series.ImageModality values that are actual acquisition modalities, i.e. those in the DICOM Context Group 29 (value set OID 1.2.840.10008.6.1.19)
